# contracts/ — keeps this directory tracked (checked in)
#
# contracts/ is the repository's external-facing API surface. See:
#   docs/adr/repository/api-contracts.md          (code ctr — what contracts are; contract testing)
#   docs/adr/repository/conventional-folders.md   (rule ADR-FOLDERS:11 — the folder convention)
#
# Layout: contracts/<contract-name>/v<N>/
#   - <contract-name>/ is the named boundary (the unit), like infrastructure/templates/<name>/.
#   - v<N> are version folders: integers, no leading zeros (v1, v2, … v10).
#   - Declared, live versions start at v1. v0 is reserved for internal/draft use and is never
#     declared as a live version; zero-padded forms (v01, v000) are never used.
#   - A published version (v1+) is immutable; an incompatible change is a new v<N>. Each version
#     folder carries its own .gitkeep. Coexisting versions are deliberate and equally live
#     (ADR-ONELIVE:7), not legacy.
